query.result:
English:
124 As when, gathering corn or tares, 125 the doves, gathered together for their feeding, 126 are quiet, without showing their usual pride,
127 if something appears that frightens them, 128 they suddenly leave their food, 129 because they are assailed by a greater care;
130 so I saw that fresh company 131 leave their song, and flee toward the shore, 132 like a man who goes, and does not know where he will end up;
133 nor was our departure any less swift.
